A long pause. "Well, sir... I don't see a Klaus Schmidt on our registry, but perhaps your brother chose to be discreet--perhaps a wife at home?" He laughed inappropriately.\par
"Yes, Klaus married. But he very fat. His wife no lie with him." Becker rolled his eyes at himself reflected in the booth. \i If Susan could hear me now, \i0 he thought. "I fat and lonely too. I want lie with her. Pay lots of money."\par
Becker was giving an impressive performance, but he'd gone too far. Prostitution was illegal in Spain, and Se\'f1or Rold\'e1n was a careful man. He'd been burned before by Guardia officials posing as eager tourists. \i I want lie with her. \i0 Rold\'e1n knew it was a setup. If he said yes, he would be heavily fined and, as always, forced to provide one of his most talented escorts to the police commissioner free of charge for an entire weekend.\par
When Rold\'e1n spoke, his voice not quite as friendly. "Sir, this is Escortes Bel\'e9n. May I ask who's calling?"\par
