"What are you working on?" Hale asked, trying a different approach.\par
Susan said nothing.\par
"Some team player \i you\i0  are. Sure I can't have a peek?" Hale stood and started moving around the circle of terminals toward her.\par
Susan sensed that Hale's curiosity had the potential to cause some serious problems today. She made a snap decision. "It's a diagnostic," she offered, falling back on the commander's lie.\par
Hale stopped in his tracks. "Diagnostic?" He sounded doubtful. "You're spending Saturday running a diagnostic instead of playing with the prof?"\par
"His name is David."\par
