Susan now understood why the Sys-Sec was so concerned. \i Mutation strings\i0 , she mused. She knew mutation strings were programming sequences that corrupted data in extremely complex ways. They were very common in computer viruses, particularly viruses that altered large blocks of data. Of course, Susan also knew from Tankado's E-mail that the mutation strings Chartrukian had seen were harmless--simply part of Digital Fortress.\par
