Normally, bypassing Gauntlet was unthinkable. In this situation, however, there was no danger in sending Digital Fortress directly into TRANSLTR; the commander knew exactly what the file was and where it came from.\par
"With all due respect, sir," Chartrukian pressed, "I've never heard of a diagnostic that employs mutation--"\par
