Susan forgot about Hale for an instant. She prayed the caller was David. \i Tell me he's okay, \i0 she thought. \i Tell me he found the ring!\i0  But Strathmore caught her eye and he gave her a frown. It was not David.\par
Susan felt her breath grow short. All she wanted to know was that the man she loved was safe. Strathmore, Susan knew, was impatient for other reasons; if David took much longer, the commander would have to send backup--NSA field agents. It was a gamble he had hoped to avoid.\par
"Commander?" Chartrukian urged. "I really think we should check--"\par
