\pard\nowidctlpar\sb100\sa100 Upstairs, Strathmore held the Beretta in his hand. He reread his note and laid it on the floor of the room where he was standing. What he was about to do was a cowardly act, there was no doubt. \i I'm a survivor, \i0 he thought. He thought of the virus in the NSA databank, he thought of David Becker in Spain, he thought of his plans for a back door. He had told so many lies. He was guilty of so much. He knew this was the only way to avoid accountability... the only way to avoid the shame. Carefully he aimed the gun. Then he closed his eyes and pulled the trigger.\par
