\pard\nowidctlpar\sb100\sa100\kerning0\b0\fs24\par
Susan staggered out of Node 3.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\sb100\sa100\qc SUBJECT: DAVID BECKER--TERMINATED\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\sb100\sa100 As if in a dream, she moved toward Crypto's main exit. Greg Hale's voice echoed in her mind: \i Susan, Strathmore's going to kill me! Susan, the commander's in love with you!\i0\par
Susan reached the enormous circular portal and began stabbing desperately at the keypad. The door did not move. She tried again, but the enormous slab refused to rotate. Susan let out a muted scream--apparently the power outage had deleted the exit codes. She was still trapped.\par
Without warning, two arms closed around her from behind, grasping her half-numb body. The touch was familiar yet repulsive. It lacked the brute strength of Greg Hale, but there was a desperate roughness to it, an inner determination like steel.\par
Susan turned. The man restraining her was desolate, frightened. It was a face she had never seen.\par
"Susan," Strathmore begged, holding her. "I can explain."\par
She tried to pull away.\par
The commander held fast.\par
Susan tried to scream, but she had no voice. She tried to run, but strong hands restrained her, pulling her backward.\par
"I love you," the voice was whispering. "I've loved you forever."\par
Susan's stomach turned over and over.\par
"Stay with me."\par
Susan's mind whirled with grisly images--David's bright-green eyes, slowly closing for the last time; Greg Hale's corpse seeping blood onto the carpet; Phil Chartrukian's burned and broken on the generators.\par
"The pain will pass," the voice said. "You'll love again."\par
Susan heard nothing.\par
"Stay with me," the voice pleaded. "I'll heal your wounds."\par
